iPhone 14 ‚Üí iPhone 17

iPhone 14 Series (Released 2022)
Overview

The iPhone 14 series focused on safety features, camera processing improvements, and introduced Dynamic Island on Pro models.

Safety & Security

Emergency SOS via Satellite (first iPhone generation to include this)

Crash Detection using high-g accelerometer and gyroscope

Face ID on all models (no Touch ID)



iPhone 14 / iPhone 14 Plus

Positioning: Reliable everyday iPhones with strong battery life and OLED displays.

Display:

iPhone 14: 6.1" OLED, 60Hz

iPhone 14 Plus: 6.7" OLED, 60Hz

Chip: A15 Bionic (same version used in iPhone 13 Pro)

Camera:

12MP Main (f/1.5)

12MP Ultra Wide

Photonic Engine for improved low-light photos

Design: Classic notch design

Build: Aerospace-grade aluminium

Battery life:

iPhone 14: up to 20 hours video

iPhone 14 Plus: up to 26 hours video



iPhone 14 Pro / iPhone 14 Pro Max

Positioning: Major step forward in display and camera technology.

Chip: A16 Bionic (first 4nm iPhone chip)

Display:

ProMotion 1‚Äì120Hz

Always-On Display

Dynamic Island (replaced the notch)

Camera system:

48MP Main camera (first 48MP iPhone)

3x optical zoom

ProRAW support

Action Mode video

Cinematic Mode up to 4K 30fps

Build: Surgical-grade stainless steel

Battery life:

iPhone 14 Pro: up to 23 hours video

iPhone 14 Pro Max: up to 29 hours video

Charging & Connectivity (All iPhone 14 Models)

Lightning port (USB 2.0 speeds)

MagSafe up to 15W

US models are eSIM-only (no physical SIM tray)

Colours

Midnight

Starlight

Blue

Purple

Red

Yellow (added Spring 2023)



iPhone 15 Series (Released 2023)
Overview

The iPhone 15 series introduced USB-C across all models and major camera upgrades, especially on Pro models.

Shared Features (All Models)

USB-C charging (Lightning removed)

Dynamic Island on all models

MagSafe and Qi2 wireless charging

Supports wired reverse charging (low-power accessories)

iPhone 15 / iPhone 15 Plus

Positioning: Modern everyday iPhones with excellent cameras.

Display:

6.1" (15) / 6.7" (15 Plus)

OLED, 60Hz

Up to 2000 nits outdoor brightness

Chip: A16 Bionic

Camera:

48MP Main with 2x optical-quality zoom

12MP Ultra Wide

Build: Aluminium frame with colour-infused glass back

USB-C speed: USB 2.0 (480 Mbps)

Battery life:

iPhone 15: up to 20 hours video

iPhone 15 Plus: up to 26 hours video

iPhone 15 Pro / iPhone 15 Pro Max

Positioning: Performance-focused Pro devices with advanced video and photography.

Chip: A17 Pro (3nm, first ‚ÄúPro‚Äù-branded chip)

RAM: 8GB (required for Apple Intelligence)

Build: Grade 5 titanium frame (lighter than stainless steel)

Display:

ProMotion 120Hz

Always-On Display

Camera system:

48MP Main with ProRAW

3x optical zoom (Pro)

5x optical tetraprism zoom (Pro Max)

ProRes video up to 4K 60fps to external storage

Controls:

Action Button (replaced mute switch)

USB-C speed: USB 3.2 Gen 2 (up to 10Gbps)



iPhone 16 / 16 Plus (Released 2024)
Overview

The iPhone 16 series focused on AI readiness, camera usability, and refined hardware controls.

Display:

6.1" (16) / 6.7" (Plus)

OLED, up to 2000 nits

Chip: A18

RAM: 8GB (required for Apple Intelligence)

Storage: 128GB / 256GB / 512GB

Battery life:

iPhone 16: up to 22 hours video

iPhone 16 Plus: up to 27 hours video

Camera

48MP Fusion Main camera with 2x optical-quality zoom

12MP Ultra Wide with autofocus

Macro photography supported

Spatial photo and video capture for Apple Vision Pro

Hardware Controls

Camera Control button (sapphire tactile button for zoom, focus, exposure)

Action Button (customisable shortcuts)

AI & Durability

Apple Intelligence features:

Writing tools

Photo Clean Up

Genmoji

Visual Intelligence via Camera Control

Ceramic Shield (50% tougher than first generation)

IP68 water resistance

Connectivity:

Wi-Fi 7

Bluetooth 5.3

MagSafe up to 25W

eSIM-only in the US

iPhone 16 Pro / 16 Pro Max (Released 2024)
Overview

The most advanced iPhones of their generation, focused on performance, video, and photography.

Build: Grade 5 titanium with matte glass back

Display:

Pro: 6.3"

Pro Max: 6.9" (largest iPhone display to date)

Always-On OLED with ProMotion 120Hz

2000 nits peak / 1 nit minimum

Performance

Chip: A18 Pro

RAM: 8GB LPDDR5X

Improved thermal design with aluminium substructure

Storage:

Pro: 128GB ‚Üí 1TB

Pro Max: 256GB ‚Üí 1TB

Camera System

48MP Main Fusion with 2nd-gen sensor-shift OIS

48MP Ultra Wide (major upgrade from 12MP)

12MP Telephoto with 5x optical zoom (on both Pro models)

Video:

4K 120fps Dolby Vision

Pro-level audio recording with Audio Mix modes

Battery

iPhone 16 Pro: up to 27 hours video

iPhone 16 Pro Max: up to 33 hours video (best in iPhone history)

Colours

Black Titanium

White Titanium

Natural Titanium

Desert Titanium



